_:B38441010e25a09feb7caef1e9b428ab5 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> "(In mammalian testis) Along the way (the sperm travel), three accessory sex glands, the seminal vesicle, prostate, and bulbourethral (Cowper's) gland, respectively, add their secretions as sperm move from the testes to the urethra.[well established][VHOG]" .
