_:B2fde2a10e1482502bbdb204c67dc2b43 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> "In tetrapods, the urinary bladder arises as an outpocketing of the cloaca. (...) The tetrapod urinary bladder appears first among amphibians and is present in Sphenodon, turtles, most lizards, ostriches among birds, and all mammals.[well established][VHOG]" .
