_:Bfbf19181b5ff78f0106c97007206c59d <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> "A gland that secretes products (excluding hormones and other chemical messengers) into ducts (duct glands) which lead directly into the external environment[WP]. Typical exocrine glands include sweat glands, salivary glands, mammary glands, stomach, liver, pancreas." .
